<div class="rule"></div>
<section id="faq" style="padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:#050D05;">
  <div style="max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="lbl">Claude for Business — FAQ</span>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,2.6rem);font-weight:400;color:#F0FFF0;line-height:1.2;max-width:680px;margin-bottom:3rem;">
      Every question we get about implementing Claude.
    </h2>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;max-width:860px;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;" open>
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          What does it mean to implement Claude in a business?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Implementing Claude means going beyond buying seats. It means training your team to use Claude effectively, configuring Claude Projects with your brand voice and company context, building documented workflows for your highest-leverage tasks, and creating a prompt library your team actually uses. Most companies buy Claude and get 20% of its capability. Implementation closes that gap.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          What is Claude AI and how can businesses use it?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Claude is an AI assistant made by Anthropic, designed for complex reasoning, long documents, and nuanced writing. Businesses use it for content production at scale, sales outreach personalization, competitive research, customer communication drafting, internal knowledge Q&A, meeting prep and follow-up, and building AI-native workflows. It's especially strong for B2B companies with high-volume writing, analysis, and research tasks.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          What is a Claude Project and why does it matter for teams?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Claude Projects is a feature in Claude's paid plans that gives Claude persistent context — your brand voice, company background, ICP definition, style guides, and custom instructions — so every conversation starts with that context already loaded. For teams, this means every output is on-brand from the first draft. No more re-explaining your business in every session. Implementation includes setting up and configuring Projects for your specific function.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          What's the difference between Claude Teams and Claude Enterprise?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Claude Teams is Anthropic's paid plan for groups — shared Projects, team management, and higher usage limits. Claude Enterprise adds SSO, audit logs, expanded context windows (up to 500K tokens), and deeper data integrations. Most B2B companies at $5M–$50M start with Teams. We assess which plan fits based on your use cases and team size during the scoping call.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to implement Claude for a business?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Team training can be completed in a single half-day session — your team leaves with working prompts, configured Claude Projects, and documented workflows the same day. Full workflow implementation, where we build Claude into your core business processes and automations, typically takes 4–8 weeks depending on complexity. Most clients see measurable output improvement within the first week after training.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          Do I need technical staff to implement Claude?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">For team training and Claude Projects configuration — no. This is non-technical work any team can complete. For building Claude-powered workflows connected to your existing tools (CRM, email platforms, databases), some technical involvement helps but is not required. We've built working Claude workflows for non-technical teams using Make, Zapier, and Airtable alongside the Claude API.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          Can Claude access my company's internal data and documents?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Yes, in several ways. Claude Projects lets you upload documents, SOPs, and reference materials that persist across conversations. Claude Enterprise supports deeper integrations. For real-time data access, Claude can be connected to internal systems via the Claude API integrated with tools like Make or custom builds. We assess your data environment and design the right approach during scoping.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          What does a Claude workflow look like in practice?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">A Claude workflow automates a repeating business task using Claude as the intelligence layer. Example: a sales workflow that pulls account data from your CRM, runs it through Claude for research and personalization, and outputs a drafted sequence into your email tool — triggered automatically for every new qualified account. We document and build these as repeatable systems, not one-off experiments.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          How is Claude different from ChatGPT for business use?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Both are capable, but they differ meaningfully for business use. Claude has a significantly longer context window (up to 200K tokens on Teams, 500K on Enterprise), making it better for long documents, contracts, and extensive research. Claude tends to produce more nuanced, less generic writing — important for brand-specific content. Claude Projects provides persistent team context that ChatGPT's equivalent doesn't replicate as cleanly. Many organizations use both for different tasks.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          How do I measure ROI on Claude implementation?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">The clearest metrics are time-per-task reduction (how long does it take to produce X before and after), output volume per person, and cost per deliverable. We establish baseline measurements before implementation and track against them. Most teams see 50–80% reduction in time on their highest-volume tasks within 30 days. Secondary metrics include quality consistency, team adoption rates, and reduction in external agency spend.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.5rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;color:#F0FFF0;cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
          Who leads the implementation at Treetop?
          <span style="color:#00C853;font-size:1.2rem;flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#8FAF8F;line-height:1.8;margin-top:1rem;padding-right:2rem;">Bill Colbert leads all Claude implementation engagements. Bill runs four businesses using Claude as the operational backbone — this isn't theoretical training. It's implementation from someone who uses Claude daily for marketing, research, content, and revenue workflows across multiple business contexts. Every prompt library, Claude Project configuration, and workflow we build comes from systems that are actually running in production.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

